description:
&lt;p&gt;We are offering a fantastic career opportunity as a Sister/Charge Nurse in an exciting, forward thinking specialist respiratory Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for experienced and dynamic nurse to lead our workforce and set and maintain the high clinical standards we all aspire to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require energetic, self-motivated and innovative individuals who are passionate about Respiratory care nursing and who are willing to push the professional boundaries to develop an exceptional service for our patients. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants must have: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Intensive care / High Dependency care Course &lt;br /&gt;• Extensive clinical leadership/team management experience &lt;br /&gt;• Expert skills in caring for both Level 2 and Level 3 patients&lt;br /&gt;• A Degree or equivalent level of education and experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About our Service &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lane Fox Respiratory Unit is the largest weaning and home mechanical ventilation centre in the UK. We provide management and long term follow up for patients with chronic respiratory disease such as COPD and neuro-muscular diseases. The Lane Fox Respiratory Unit also offers specialist nurse lead clinics and a home ventilation service for assessing and advising patients with chronic respiratory illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our unique, purpose built 14 bedded unit delivers highly quality specialised respiratory care to complex level 2 and level 3 patients including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tracheostomy management and mechanical ventilation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weaning from invasive mechanical ventilation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acute and chronic non-invasive ventilation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High Flow oxygen therapy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you share our vision to help patients with respiratory failure to live independently this is the perfect job for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here’s what our staff say about us…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;“It doesn’t matter how challenging the day is, if you got the team around you, you feel like you can do anything!”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;“I love coming to work supporting patients with such specialised needs who come into our unit unable to breathe and leave fully independent.”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;“People ask me why I have been here for so long and I say to them I love my job, I love the patients and there is nowhere in the world I would go and be satisfied that would compare to how we work in Lane Fox“&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you a personalised induction programme with supervision and support from our dedicated practice development team and one to one support from the senior nursing team. We have excellent development programme with protected learning time including support to develop leadership and management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome you to contact us to find out more about the role .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020 (midnight)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
